---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Revise and edit"
  description="Layered revision: global message through chapters, sections, paragraphs, and sentences."
>
  <p class="back-link"><a href={`${base}writing/`}>← Writing</a></p>
  <h1>Revise and edit</h1>
  <p class="page-desc">
    Revise in layers, paying attention to one level at a time. First do a global revision and ignore everything else,
    then move on to the next level.
  </p>

  <article class="revise-content">
    <section class="revise-intro">
      <p>
        When most people revise their writing, they tend to spend most of their time on levels 4 and 5, when in fact
        levels 1–3 are the most important. This is because it is useless to write a document with impeccable spelling
        and grammar if it has a confusing message.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Level 1: Global</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You first revise by checking if the global message comes through clearly and that the framework makes sense.</li>
        <li>Check that the introduction clearly provides context and pre-reveals the global message.</li>
        <li>
          Check that the conclusion reveals the global message and that it is the same as the message pre-revealed in
          the introduction.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Level 2: Chapters (one chapter at a time, if you have chapters)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Ensure that all the chapters&rsquo; messages are derived from the global message.</li>
        <li>Does each chapter&rsquo;s message come through clearly?</li>
        <li>Does the framework used in the chapter organise the ideas correctly?</li>
        <li>
          Check that the introduction of each chapter clearly provides context and pre-reveals the chapter&rsquo;s message.
          Check that the conclusion reveals the chapter&rsquo;s message and that it is the same as the message pre-revealed in
          the introduction.
        </li>
        <li>Are all chapters clearly connected?</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Level 3: Sections</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Ensure that in every chapter all the sections&rsquo; messages are derived from the chapter message.</li>
        <li>Does each section&rsquo;s message come through clearly?</li>
        <li>Does the framework used for each section organise the ideas correctly?</li>
        <li>
          Check that the introduction of each section clearly provides context and pre-reveals the section&rsquo;s message.
          Check that the conclusion reveals the section&rsquo;s message and that it is the same as the message pre-revealed in
          the introduction.
        </li>
        <li>Are all sections in the chapter clearly connected?</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Level 4: Paragraphs</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Ensure that in every section all the paragraphs&rsquo; messages are derived from the section message.</li>
        <li>Does every paragraph have a single message (only one message)?</li>
        <li>Is every paragraph correctly organised?</li>
        <li>Is every paragraph clearly linked to the previous paragraph?</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Level 5: Sentences</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Does every sentence clearly flow from the previous sentence?</li>
        <li>Check grammar.</li>
        <li>Check spelling.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .back-link {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .back-link a {
    color: var(--color-maroon);
  }
  .page-desc {
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }
  .revise-content {
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .revise-intro {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .revise-intro p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .revise-content section {
    margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
  }
  .revise-content section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .revise-content h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
    line-height: 1.35;
  }
  .revise-content ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .revise-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .revise-content li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
</style>
